==English==
=== Adjective ===
'''performant''' ([[comparative]]: ''more performant'', [[superlative]]: ''most performant'')

# Capable of achieving an adequate or excellent level of [[performance]]; [[high-performing]].
#* ''Ours is a '''performant''' network monitoring and systems monitoring tool.''
#* ''This is the most '''performant''' car I've ever owned.''

== French ==
=== Adjective ===
'''performant'''

# [[Efficient]]; [[effective]]; [[successful]].

===Usage notes===
This word is not found in any published dictionary, and is therefore regarded as incorrect. To avoid controversy, 'high-performing' or 'efficient' or 'effective' or 'successful' or [[great]] are preferred.